Analysis of personal connections in the digital age. Focus on romantic relationships, friendships, families and other social relationships. Topics include identity, intimacy, and relationship development. Course Information: Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=COMM%20101" title="COMM&#160;101" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'COMM 101');">COMM&#160;101</a> and <a href="/search/?P=COMM%20103" title="COMM&#160;103" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'COMM 103');">COMM&#160;103</a>; and Credit or concurrent registration in <a href="/search/?P=COMM%20102" title="COMM&#160;102" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'COMM 102');">COMM&#160;102</a>; and Credit or concurrent registration in <a href="/search/?P=COMM%20200" title="COMM&#160;200" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'COMM 200');">COMM&#160;200</a>.<br />
