<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>COMM&#160;423.  Discourse and Rhetoric.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Exploration of interconnections between language and social practices with attention to multiple components of discursive situations: senders, receivers, context, code, media, and content. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=COMM%20301" title="COMM&#160;301" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'COMM 301');">COMM&#160;301</a>.<br />
